import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].min(), color='red', label=f"Min: {data['x'].min().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].max(), color='blue', label=f"Max: {data['x'].max().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lumosity'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lumosity'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lumosity', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['lumosity'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    sns.countplot(x='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count?', wrap=True)

    return plt;
